<TITLE> Valentine's day vengeance </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PARIS, Feb 14 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)--A French farmer offers pots of cow dung by post for people who want to send a less than loving Valentine's day message. French entrepreneur Olivier Legrand is turning cow dung into the must-have Valentine's Day gift for those who want to send a less-than-adoring message to someone they definitely don't love. For 14 Euros he'll pack and post a charming gift box generously stuffed with the droppings of his neighbour's sizeable bovine herd. And it looks like there's a lot of angry broken hearts out there. Legrand says he's sold more than 600 of the undesirable offerings in the past three months. SOUNDBITE: Olivier Legrand, founder of Fumier.com, saying (French): "Imagine a young lady who has just been dumped by her boyfriend. She doesn't quite know what to do to get revenge. So, if you've just been ditched, take revenge and send a box of cow dung to your ex who is, in fact, the real stinker for dumping you just before Valentine's Day." Legrand and farmer Roger Combotte have set up a company called Fumier.com to market their steaming stockpile. The name has a double meaning - it's French for 'manure' but it also translates rather handily as an insulting expletive. It adds a whole new meaning to adage 'rose are red, violets are blue'.... 'ditched by your lover...say it with poo.&
